(231654, 7231, 221145, 'Birdshooter007', 3199, '', 1323971272, '[QUOTE=fluffmaster;221145]the rules for carrying air guns from any where else in the world are not pakistani rules, but the rules of that country., USA will never allow that,,,its only from dubai that u can get an air gun and bring it along in ur luggage as most of us already know[/QUOTE]\n\n   I''ve got some info for you all. \n The process for bringing an airgun from USA to Pakistan in your luggage is easy, I was of the opinion that it is possible, but some members weren''t. \n Well, you have to go to the airport at least 2 weeks prior to your flight, fill in a form (mention the kind of airgun, accessories you are carrying, # of ammo/pellets, etc), and deposit it with the airport authorities.\n When you go to the airport for the flight, pack your airgun in your luggage, get it sealed, or whatever, and down it goes into the plane''s fuselage. \n Hope it helps and your queries are rightly answered.', 1, 1, '119.73.10.130', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
