(233548, 7797, 232382, 'SalmanHusain', 1825, '', 1324746886, 'officially both are different thing!! calibre is measured in inches. caliber is equal to one inch where as 0.5 equal to 1/2 inch and 0.30 equal to 30/100th of an inch. where as bore is much more complicated. it doesnt refer to diameter of the barrel but actually some gas pressure and some calculation thing. as the bore number increase the barrel dia decrease. bore are available in 10, 12, 16, 20, 24, and 410 respectively 10 being largest and 410 being smallest. \n"the gauge of a firearm is a unit of measurement used to express the diameter of the barrel. Gauge is determined from the weight of a solid sphere of lead that will fit the bore of the firearm, and is expressed as the multiplicative inverse of the sphere''s weight as a fraction of a pound (e.g., a 1&#8260;12th pound ball fits a 12-gauge bore). Thus there are twelve 12-gauge balls per pound (etc.). The term is related to the measurement of cannon, which were also measured by the weight of their iron round shot; an 8 pounder would fire an 8 lb (3.6 kg) spherical cast iron ball and had a bore diameter of about 91 mm (3.6 in).'' copied from wikipedia. \ngauge and bore is one and the same thing. its actually we Pakistani wrongly speak ''tees-bore'' in reality internationally its thirty caliber or .30th inch. such is the case is for SMG, internationally smg refers to mp5 or any sub compact rapidfire gun where as in Pakistan it refers to Chinese AK47. also one more example, German Shepherd dog(GSD) and Alsation are one and the same thing but in Pakistan we refer alsation to local breed bhagyari or an east german line GSD as alsation or any dog that resembles jackal or wolf. :)', 1, 1, '182.178.58.73', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
