(235126, 5797, 227853, 'PakistanFirst', 5092, '', 1325390337, 'SHOT GUNNER,\n\nI don''t know of any single-barrel rifle manufacturer  that stamps on the rifle barrel "22LR/22WMR"  or similar markings indicating that 22LR and 22 magnum cartridges can be fired in that rifle. The cartridge and chamber dimensions of the two calibers are different. One may be able to insert a 22LR cartridge into a 22 magnum rifle.  Firing such a combination is asking for trouble on two counts. First - the rim of the 22LR cartridge may blow up. Second - with long chamber (22 mag) and a short cartridge (22LR) the chamber will be ruined over time.  \n\nSound safety advise for myself and others- never, ever fire a cartridge in a rifle that is not designed for that cartridge.', 1, 1, '75.139.232.176', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
