(239918, 7982, 238134, 'findlj', 6519, '', 1326747803, 'Ejector update!   I have some good news.   Hopefully this will help any new Baikal IZH 27 owners.  \n\n I''ve run about another 40 rounds of a different Winchester AA shell through the Baikal today.  Guess what, it''s started ejecting shells out!  It is ejecting rounds just fired probably 90% of the time out of the top barrel, 50% from the bottom barrel. Here''s what I''ve found to be true so far.\n\n   First, I certainly had the ejector selector screw set incorrectly initially.    \n   Secondly, you cannot test the ejectors with cold, spent shells effectively, it still doesn''t eject those!   Again, it is ejecting shells just fired now.\n   Thirdly, my Remington SPR 310/Baikal IZH 27 required some break-in before the ejectors start working.   \n\nThanks for everyones'' help.   I think this issue will resolve itself over time now.   I learned a lot from my PakGun friends.', 1, 0, '76.2.172.228', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
