(240398, 8037, 239973, '12GAUGE', 608, '', 1326915516, 'Bro, effective range of a firearm is kind of a tricky subject. there are many variables that are involved specially when talking about multiple projectile firearm such as a shotgun for example:\r\n\r\n1. Shot number\r\n2. degree of choke\r\n3. length of the cartridge\r\n4. shot placement\r\n5. number of pellets that hit the target\r\n6. Number of shots fired\r\n\r\ngenerally speaking:\r\n\r\na buckshot cartridge (SG/LG 2.75inch) fired from a cylinder choke (no choke) shotgun will probably and effectively put any BG down at 15 yards or less. assuming that the BG get a full cartridge load at chest.\r\n\r\nif you wish to extend that range any further than that then you will have to the increase the choke constriction or go to 3inch or longer cartridge. but in most cases, the range will not be any more than 25 yards because Primarily, shotguns are short range firearms. their biggest weakness is also their biggest strength. if you switch to a single projectile (slugs) you might be able to extend the effective range to 100 yards but sort of a kills the very purpose of a shotgun. plus it is also very difficult to aim at that distance and you''ll probably be better served with a rifle for that kind of a distance to target.\r\n\r\nshotguns may be short range weapons but within their effective range, their lethality is second to none. any BG shot with a blast of 9 pellets of OO buck will certainly find himself pushing up daisies.\r\n\r\nRegards.', 1, 1, '182.177.19.167', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
