(240403, 8048, 240263, '12GAUGE', 608, '', 1326917229, 'AoA Everybody\r\n\r\nwith Baikals anything is possible. I too have seen some Baikal shotguns that are supplied with 5 choke tubes. infact I have recently purchased a shotgun for a friend that had 5 choke tubes in the factory supplied cardboard box.\r\n\r\nas for the barrel length, I would highly recommend that you take a good hard look at the intended purpose of the shotgun. if you want use it for upland hunting or skeet, I would strongly suggest 26inch barrel length. for waterfowling, 28inch is more preferred.\r\n\r\nfor HD, Bro! a 26inch barrel shotgun will be practically useless due to its long barrel length. ideally, the barrel length shouldn''t be longer than 21-22 inches. if HD is important for you then I would recommend that you also consider a Hatsan Escort Combo. it comes with a short barrel for HD use as well.\r\n\r\nin my humble opinion, a wooden furniture shotgun is better. you can easily alter and modify a wooden stock to your body whereas with a synthetic stock you cannot do anything to make it better suit you.\r\n\r\nfor shotguns, a good fit is a must. synthetic stock no matter how much weather proof and durable is absolutely useless if it doesn''t fit you.\r\n\r\nRegards.', 1, 1, '182.177.19.167', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
