(240591, 8049, 240587, 'Birdshooter007', 3199, '', 1326996288, '[QUOTE=raja yasir;240587]I have a diana 56 which is same technology as 54 put have other features as well,these guns have amazing accuracy as compared to any other spring powered airgun because of its recoil less action.scope does not matter any scope will work on this amazing gun.and yes you have to use heavy pellets on this gun mine work great with gamo hunters and h&n pellets,even pro hunter performs better in this gun as compared to other guns that i have.[/QUOTE]\nI''ll have to disagree on the scope part- ANY SCOPE WOULD NOT DO.\nThis gun is a scope-killer, the recoil felt by the shooter is almost non-existent but the recoil the scope faces is harsh. That is why I have suggested 4 screw single piece mounts which are certainly not easily available here. And then you''d need a good recoil proof scope with atleast 3-9X magnification. Even if one is available in the 20k''s range, that''d be a rip-off. \nThe gun is very very heavy and you''d need support. If you''ll be taking long range shots (utilizing the power in the gun) a scope would be quite beneficial.\nI am never going to use Gamo pellets, they''re the worst around. I don''t find any other imported pellets in the market other than Gamos, Iranis and Afghanis (which are all illigible for this gun).\nHowever, Diana pellets are sometimes available @Lucky Star, 200 pellet tins for Rs 500 each.\nWell you could get one as it''s a very accurate gun.\nThe choice is yours.', 1, 1, '119.73.12.248', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
