(240609, 3052, 240538, 'Mian Jee', 6552, '', 1327003423, '[QUOTE=AK47;240538]Thank you Mian Jee bro for the nice share.\n\nI must say, it look like an impressive round at 145 grains. I''d love to try out one, and the prices recently enable us to do so easier for the compatibility with our handguns.\n\n\nMy reservations with respect to 145 grains are:\n\n[B]Will they have MV enough to do a reasonable mushrooming?[/B]\n\nThe only way for 145 grainers to do so would probably be if they have a slightly increased +P kick also, as not to remain sub-sonic.\n\nI''d be interested in seeing it''s chronograph, if no mention on +P rating on the package.\n\nMoreover, I deem it would be better to use these in full barrel lengths, hence +4 inches, preferably a CZ 4.7" barrel or Beretta M9/Taurus Pt 92/99, etc. That may help to some minor extent though.\n\nKindly check and see if there''s any mention with this respect.\n\nI believe a practical test would prove it''s effectiveness, and one should not just be happy to carry a 145 grainer. Let us know from your test, if convenient to you, anytime. \n\nThanks for the share.\n\n\nRegards.[/QUOTE]\n\nI have almost all types of available JHP''s,\n\n[I](S&B 115gr, PPU 124gr, Armscore 124gr & these Barnaul 145gr)[/I]\n[I](also have the Federal Hydra Shochk 147gr but can''t test 600/Rs).\n[/I]\nI have done some tests by firing them in swimming pool from 10 feets\nand found good expansions after collecting the projectiles.(sorry for no pic''s).\n\nI think i need to do it all over again,\n\nNow back to the point,\n\nI really like this Barnaul 145gr bullet, it has a boxer primer in brass coated steel case,\nVery affordable price & easily available.\n\nI fired them from my 5" barrel pistol.\n\nI am not very good at observing deviations so can''t tell you the statistics or MV,\nBut i felt a very low recoil so i think these are subsonic rounds,\nDefinitely not a +P round & not mentioned with this respect.\n\nI really don''t wan''na kill a person in any situation, regardless he is Good,Bad or Ugly,\nI just want him to run for his life after eating one straight to the stomach \n& second in the a$$,\n\nSo IMO the heavy & low velocity HP bullet with minimum penetration is much more suitable & will do the job for my SD purpose.\n\nI think you must get some & try some as soon,\nA practical test from a overzealous person like you is much needed & eagerly awaited.\n\nRegards.', 1, 1, '182.177.156.240', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
