(240626, 8043, 240555, 'cz-duty fan', 5462, '', 1327013950, '[QUOTE=AK47;240534]Sadly, I''ve never had the opportunity to fire with a PO7-Duty, hence cannot comment here.\n\nYet, let me frankly say, unless you''ve serious range shooting in mind, the trigger should be your least cause for concern.\n \nRami''s is pretty gritty for the start, yet with the use and careful cleansing and lubing of the walls against which it''s mechanism has friction, help it''s smoothness, though slowly and gradually. Lolz, it wouldn''t even go back to normal when I first took it in my hands, all gummed up from the inside.\n\nI''d say, triggers of all quality handguns in single action mode are smooth enough for the SD concern, as long as you hear a bang with the pull. The Rami''s DA pull is relatively heavy for an accurate 1.st shot in the hands of a less regular shooter, hence I keep it[I] half-cocked[/I] and it''s pretty easy from this stance.\n\nI''ve personally not been very critical of triggers, until the Caracal trigger confirmed it to me, what it actually means to be "crisp".\n\nYet, as regards the Rami, CZ-Sp01 Tactical, etc, triggers are all the same, difference stepping in with Omega system only and the trigger of CZ-SP01 Shadow.\n\nHence, unless you''re sports interested only - [I]and I doubt you''d be so with a CZ Rami [/I]- the trigger is nothing to worry about or make comparisons with the Duty''s. Rather the size.\n\n\n\nRegards.[/QUOTE]\n\nthanks for the detailed reply:smile:\n\n[QUOTE=Asif Ali;240555][COLOR=black][FONT=sans-serif]This is what i enquired from CZ Officials while buying RAMI and to end this confusion between D and BD below is query and its reply from CZ:\nI asked:\n[B]Please let me know what is  the difference between CZ 2075 RAMI-BD and 2075 RAMI-D, since in your website  RAMI-BD is mentioned but here in Pakistan RAMI-D is written on frame instead of  RAMI-BD, please clarify? [/B]\n\n[/FONT][/COLOR][FONT=Arial][SIZE=2][COLOR=#0000ff]And CZ replied:\n[SIZE=3][B]As for RAMI BD and RAMI D - the RAMI BD is  an older description used for the US market. The pistols are the same, only the  inscription is RAMI D or RAMI BD.[/B][/SIZE][/COLOR][/SIZE][/FONT][COLOR=black][FONT=sans-serif]\n\nNow I think matter stands resolved and I will request moderators to close the thread:)\n[/FONT][/COLOR][/QUOTE]\n\nthanks:smile:', 1, 0, '119.154.186.252', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
