(240950, 8057, 240683, 'Ahnab', 6111, '', 1327136939, '[QUOTE=BaderJanjua;240683]When Americans were fighting in Phillipines in the second decade of the 20th Century it was revealed to them that at close quarters their .38 revolvers which at that point of time were Colt 38 did little to stop well determined charging Mooro warriors especiall in thick growth. Thus was born the .45. During 2nd World War tha american side Arm was Colt 1911 while the Germans carried Luger and mauser Pistols in 9 mm. It was quoted that often during close battles inside trenches the shots by Germans would end up sending the American Soldiers to field Hospitals from where a good number would recover to once again join the battle lines while the shots taken by Americans equipped with Colt 45s would just slump the Germans dead in tracks. The 1911 .45 pistols became so popular with the soldiers that they preffered to use them instead of baynots . 8 rounds of .45 at close ranges with greater maneauverability would add a tremendous punch. However this did not mean that 9 mm lost its credibility, since it is still a very favourite cal and the development of ammo like Hydra Shock and other hollowpoints for Sd purposes may set aside the former reasoning. IMHO as it is said in most law enforcement and military circles that in combat pistols should help you to get to your rifles/shotguns or at the end are good for suicide as a last resort in heavy engagement.[/QUOTE]\n\nVery interesting. Just want to point out a few corrections:-\n\n1) The Philippine-American War lasted from 1899 to 1902, and not in the second decade of the 20th century.\n2) The M1911 was developed from the Colt M1905 (first gun to be chambered for the .45 ACP) in 1908, and after several trails and modifications, was finally accepted in 1911.\n3) During the Second World War, the Germans carried primarily Walther P-38''s and (too a lesser degree) Luger P08''s, [B]NOT[/B] Mausers as sidearms. Mauser Kar-98''s were, infact, the standard rifle of the German army.\n4) Some captured M1911''s were also used by the Germans, and were given the designation  [B]"Pistole 660(a)"[/B].', 1, 1, '111.68.105.241', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
(240951, 2288, 240674, 'Fraz', 5855, '', 1327137029, '[QUOTE=gunenthusiast;240674]MOI License is obviously better as you can buy/sell weapons throughout Pakistan. It, therefore, is more costly. On the other hand a provincial All Pakistan License only allows you sale/purchase in that province.[/QUOTE]\n\nbro i have a KPK issued provincial licence which was upgraded to ALL PAK, i bought a handgun on tht lic from punjab ... so it clarifies that we can sell / buy anywhere in the country', 1, 1, '182.177.71.53', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
