(241117, 7857, 234217, 'AK47', 162, '', 1327187018, '[COLOR=#000000][I][B]Ameer wrote:[/B][/I]\n\n[/COLOR][QUOTE][SIZE=5][COLOR=#ff0000][B]@ AK-47 n all,[/B][B]\n\nWhat is Caracal Quick Acquisition Sight System?[/B][/COLOR][/SIZE][/QUOTE]\n\nAmeer bro, it is described in my review if you click a couple of pages back, and I suggested it also only for SD requirement, not for range/sports shooting, for which conventional sights models should be preferred.\n\nThe system is basically a whole new concept -[I] for quick target acquisition -[/I] in which the rear sight is placed just ahead of the ejection port, aligning in with the fibre-optics front sight ahead of it. This enables quicker target acquisition, since kind of a way you''re just aiming in with the front sight, coz the two are placed pretty close to each other.\n\nCheck the rear sight ahead of the ejection port and fibre-optics front sight, as well as the [I]raised front portion of slide[/I], which probably helps in accumulating light into the line of sight:\n\n[IMG]http://i1136.photobucket.com/albums/n497/wahstar1/PG upload/Frontsight1Small.jpg[/IMG]\n\n\n [ATTACH=CONFIG]7829[/ATTACH]\n\nThis is [I]SD specific [/I]and not to be preferred for range/sports shooting or for close grouping of shots over greater distances, i.e 15 mtrs onwards, for which the sighting variation is limited, yet for quick SD response it is commented well on by those who have used it around the world.\n\n The POI is not significantly deviated on torso shots up to 20 yards, which is more than enough of performance from an SD handgun, yet rest assured your aiming-in is very quickly dead-on from traditional SD distances.\n\n I personally found it pretty helpful for sighting-in during my rapid shot string as per video, and you may have checked already the board on which I shot those 15 rounds in 4.5 seconds, still getting a reasonably deadly deal onto it. It kind of helps keeping focused.\n\n\nRegards.', 1, 1, '119.153.67.205', 0, 1, 1, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
