(241365, 8079, 0, 'Trigger_happy78', 4053, 'Review: Akdal Mka 1919', 1327292588, 'Few days ago I went to Lahore to buy Saiga 12. Naveed bhai was kind enough to take time from his busy schedule and we started looking for saiga. There were only two pieces available in the market and the shopkeepers were charging very high prices. So we ended up buying this gun. Because only these two guns are available in Pakistan with removable mags, we have to compare them with each other. Although there is no comparison of Saiga with Akdal :). Saiga 12 is way out of its league. The Akdal Mka1919 comes in a cheap cardboard box and the packing is very un impressive. But that''s what you get with this kind of money. \n\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0138-1.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0139-1.jpg[/IMG]\n\nInside the box you get the gun itself, two mags( 2/34 and 3"),although you can use both with our normal 2 3/4 Shaheen shells. One barrel extension/ full choke and a Flash supressor and user manual. \n\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0141.jpg[/IMG]\n\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0140.jpg[/IMG]\n\nTechnical Specifications:\nModel                              : Mka1919\nCaliber.                            : 12 Guage\nOperation.                      : Gas operated, semi-auto\nWeight( empty)               : 3300 g \nOverall length.                : 40.5 inch \nHeight.                             : 7.5 inch \nBarrel length.                  : 19.7 inch \nSight radius.                    : 23.6 inch \nMagazine weight(empty) : 300 g \nMagazine capacity.         : 5 cartridges\n\nThe Akdal Mka1919 gas operating system is based on Remington 1100 platform, which is not as fast as Saiga 12''s gas system. But it is faster then most of us pulling the trigger. When disassembled, I was not impressed with the machining of the gun. But then again that''s what you expect from budget Turkish weapon. Here see what I mean. \n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0146.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0145.jpg[/IMG]\n\nDisassembling the Akdal Mka1919 is a pain***. I couldn''t even fully disassemble the gun because I didn''t have the required tools. I mean what''s with that. The handguards were very flimsy and are not very durable. \n\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0148.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0151.jpg[/IMG]\n\nThe Akdal Mka1919 gets really really dirty even after firing few rounds. That might be because of the gas operating system or it might be the Shaheen cartridges. I remember my Remington 1100 alway use to jam if not cleaned after each firing session. So I think this gun should be cleaned after each firing sessions if this is your primary HD weapon to avoid jams. See how dirty it gets after firing 50+ rounds. But one thing that I like is the quality of the barrel, its very well made and cromed from inside. \n\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0149.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0150.jpg[/IMG]\n\nThe Akdal Mka1919 is a very ergonomic and very well balanced. When held, it doesn''t feel heavy at all and very comfortable to shoot with. The recoil with Shaheen  2 3/4 SG shells is very low. It''s softer to shoot them normal pump shotguns. I''ve heard that it gives problems when firing light loads. It wasn''t the case with this one. We fired all #4,6,8 and SG/LG Shaheen cartridges with no FTFeed or FTEject. The gun comes alive when you fire it. It puts a smile on your face, it did on mine. You guys will see. When firing Mka1919 you forget about how its made or where its made you just want to keep firing and it eats all you through at it. So my conclusion is that if you can afford the insanely high prices of Saiga 12 then that''s the best money can buy period, Sauga''s firing speed is better, trigger is better, magazines are better, how can I forget the mags. The mags of Akdal Mka1919 are not good, they not well made and are very difficult to load. That''s my experience with them. Might be better to look for some aftermarket ones. Or it might get better after a while. You''ll see in the video later. For now here''s some eye candy.\n\n[IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0155.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0156.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0157.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0158.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0160.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0161.jpg[/IMG]\n [IMG]http://i1113.photobucket.com/albums/k512/bilal_qureshi1/IMAG0162.jpg[/IMG]\n\n[I][COLOR=#0000cd][B]A few Video''s \n[/B][/COLOR][/I][URL="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W2qYPJzkbgI&feature=youtube_gdata_player"]\n[/URL][video=youtube;W2qYPJzkbgI]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=W2qYPJzkbgI&amp;feature=youtube_gdata_player[/video]\n[video=youtube;mjNdef0K6Vo]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mjNdef0K6Vo&amp;feature=youtube_gdata_player[/video]\n[video=youtube;ZyNiE8Q6cSM]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZyNiE8Q6cSM&amp;feature=youtube_gdata_player[/video]\n[video=youtube;gdjuIL7ZBFY]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gdjuIL7ZBFY&amp;feature=youtube_gdata_player[/video]', 1, 0, '202.69.15.156', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
