(241898, 2353, 69332, 'AK47', 162, '', 1327430059, 'Hi! Been doing some restorations with above rifle and wanted to share here with some practical shooting also, but sadly forgot the ammo back by the hills during this summer, so will be back later with that, probably by spring.\n\nSo far, managed this as part of[I] periodic maintenance[/I] and some [I]off-time fun[/I]:\n\n[COLOR=#ff0000][I][B]Bolt Refinish:[/B][/I][/COLOR][COLOR=#000000]\n\nWent to my number-plate guy and asked him to buff it out with a soft brush over the machine, using some brasso like agent. \n\nWhen done, I took it home, cleaned it once more to wipe off the loose carbon residue from the buffing job, and then applied some steel-polish for further cleansing and shine, finally topping off with an application of auto-wax for further smoothness/protection:\n[/COLOR]\n[IMG]http://i1136.photobucket.com/albums/n497/wahstar1/Rifles/30-06015Small.jpg[/IMG]\n\n[B][COLOR=#ff0000][I]Magazine:[/I][/COLOR]\n[/B]\n[COLOR=#000000]I stripped the magazine and - after complete cleaning, [/COLOR][I]especially of the hairlike ridges by the bends of the spring which can be very prone to rust collection- greased the whole thing up with some quality white grease, reason why you can''t see the shine, otherwise it''s like new:\n\n\n[/I][IMG]http://i1136.photobucket.com/albums/n497/wahstar1/Rifles/30-06019Medium.jpg[/IMG]\n\n\n[B][COLOR=#ff0000][I]Wooden parts:[/I][/COLOR]\n[/B]\nIf you checked the 1.st page of this thread, this is how the rifle looked like back then, a couple of years back, [I]default finish[/I]:\n\n\n[IMG]http://i1136.photobucket.com/albums/n497/wahstar1/Rifles/30-062.jpg[/IMG]\n\nAnd this is what our 2 seasons -[I] hot n'' cold [/I] -can do to our guns, over a couple of years,[I] climatic effects[/I], watch the dryness/dullness of the wooden parts:\n\n[IMG]http://i1136.photobucket.com/albums/n497/wahstar1/Rifles/30-06012Small.jpg[/IMG]\n\nI did not go for any special oils/agents, wanted the job done without too many deliberations, and since it''s a keeper and I care nil for market status of the gun, I called in my preferred polish guy to give it it''s required dose, neither more nor less, to get it back to it''s original status as per picture above, you can compare, it''s smooth and silk now, just a few swabs of almost colorless polish and some quality lamination:\n\n\n[IMG]http://i1136.photobucket.com/albums/n497/wahstar1/Rifles/30-06018Small.jpg[/IMG]\n\n[IMG]http://i1136.photobucket.com/albums/n497/wahstar1/Rifles/30-062.jpg[/IMG]\n\nNow looking for some ammo, a shell carrier, a sling and a new butt-plate.\n\nRegards.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n[COLOR=#000000]\n\n[/COLOR]', 1, 1, '119.153.58.250', 0, 1, 0, 0, 0, 'on_nl2br', 0, 0),
